properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 11 at 9:34PM EST until January 12 at 4:00PM EST by NWS Gray ME
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 10 to 25 mph with scattered gusts up to
50 mph expected.

* WHERE...Sullivan, Merrimack, Cheshire, Eastern Hillsborough,
Interior Rockingham, Coastal Rockingham and Western and
Central Hillsborough Counties.

* WHEN...From 6 AM to 4 PM EST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A cold front will approach from the west
tonight and may be accompanied by some heavy showers and
possibly a thunderstorm around and just after daybreak. These
may produce some gusts around 50 MPH. Thereafter, scattered
gusts to 50 mph are expected from late morning through mid
afternoon. Higher elevations are most susceptible.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO 4 PM EST SUNDAY
